        ", Vaucluse, France, where he had lived.  His friend Sartre read a eulogy, paying tribute to Camuss heroic stubborn humanism .              Camuss first publication was a play Revolte dans les Asturies  written with three friends in May 1936. The subject was the 1934 revolt by Spanish miners that was brutally suppressed by the Spanish government resulting in 1,500 to 2,000 deaths. In May 1937 he wrote his first book, LEnvers et lEndroit . Both were published by ": null
