    },
    {
        " after Arab revolts against French mistreatment, Camus was one of only a few mainland journalists to visit the colony. He wrote a series of articles reporting on conditions, and advocating for French reforms and concessions to the demands of the Algerian people.     When the Algerian War began in 1954, Camus was confronted with a moral dilemma. He identified with the Pieds-Noirs such as his own parents and defended the French governments actions against the revolt. He argued the Algerian uprising was an integral part of the new ": null
    },
    {
        "Arab imperialism": "Arab Imperialism"
    },
    {
